Sentencas: The optimal sintering trajectories of three-dimensional (3D) yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) tapes were prepared using a dynamic optimization method under the controlled sintering strain.
Titulo: Optimal Control of the Sintering Strain Rate of Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolytes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Using a Thermal-Mechanical Analyzer during the Sintering Process

Sentencas: The sintering process model was carried out by the combination of both the heat transport equation and the dynamic equation of the sintering strain rate, constructed by thermal-mechanical analyzer (TMA) data.
Titulo: Optimal Control of the Sintering Strain Rate of Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolytes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Using a Thermal-Mechanical Analyzer during the Sintering Process

Sentencas: The heating pathway of a constrained strain rate case was determined numerically and was further experimentally carried out by the TMA test.
Titulo: Optimal Control of the Sintering Strain Rate of Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolytes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Using a Thermal-Mechanical Analyzer during the Sintering Process

Sentencas: Results show that the distribution of the strain rate in the ceramic tape was influenced by the sample size and heating conditions.
Titulo: Optimal Control of the Sintering Strain Rate of Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolytes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Using a Thermal-Mechanical Analyzer during the Sintering Process

Sentencas: The optimally sintered YSZ electrolyte showed better electronic performance than those with constant heating rates based on the conductivity tests.
Titulo: Optimal Control of the Sintering Strain Rate of Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolytes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Using a Thermal-Mechanical Analyzer during the Sintering Process

Sentencas: Therefore, the formation of the strain rate can be one of the factors that influenced the quality of the YSZ electrolyte in the sintering process.
Titulo: Optimal Control of the Sintering Strain Rate of Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolytes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Using a Thermal-Mechanical Analyzer during the Sintering Process
